newsitem.title: USA: Nebraska fed cattle moderate $113/dressed - USDA.
newsitem.headline: Nebraska fed cattle moderate $113/dressed - USDA.

text.p: Trade was moderately active on Thursday, USDA said. Buyer inquiry and demand good. Seller interest light as most have sold their lists already.
Dressed Basis Delivered. (paid on hot carcass weights) Steers and heifers steady.
Dressed Basis Steers - Select and Choice 2-3 1250-1350 lbs 113.00. Dressed Basis Heifers - Select and Choice 2-3 1100-1250 lbs 113.00.
Live basis sales - Equivalent 3 percent shrink delivered and FOB, some FOB 4% shrink.
Slaughter Steers - Select and Choice 2-3 1200-1350 lbs 70.00-71.00. Slaughter Heifers - Select and Choice 2-3 1100-1250 lbs 70.00-71.00.

For the week - Slaughter steers and heifers on a live basis steady to 1.00 lower, dressed basis 1.00 lower. Weekly total includes 3,200 formulated and/or contracted cattle. Confirmed - 4,200 Last Week - 23,100 Last Year - 7,800 Wk To Date- 53,800 Sm Pd Lst Wk- 48,700 Sm Pd Lst Yr- 65,000
